# 10. Créer le self-signed Issuer pour lab

Pour lab sans le vrai domain , donc on utilise  self-signed certificate.

```bash
cat > selfsigned-issuer.yaml <<EOF
apiVersion: cert-manager.io/v1
kind: Issuer
metadata:
  name: broapp-selfsigned
  namespace: ${APP_NS}
spec:
  selfSigned: {}
EOF
```

Apply:

```bash
kubectl apply -f selfsigned-issuer.yaml
```

Check:

```bash
kubectl get issuer -n $APP_NS
```

