# 11. Créer values TLS pour  notre  Helm chart 

```bash
cat > values-ingress-tls.yaml <<EOF
service:
  type: ClusterIP
  port: 80

ingress:
  enabled: true
  className: nginx
  annotations:
    cert-manager.io/issuer: broapp-selfsigned
    nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/ssl-redirect: "true"
  hosts:
    - host: ${HOST}
      paths:
        - path: /
          pathType: Prefix
  tls:
    - secretName: broapp-tls
      hosts:
        - ${HOST}
EOF
```

Upgrade app:

## Si chart local:

```bash
helm upgrade $APP_RELEASE ./broapp \
  -n $APP_NS \
  -f values-ingress-tls.yaml \
  --atomic \
  --wait \
  --timeout 10m
```

## Si chart du ACR OCI:

```bash
helm upgrade $APP_RELEASE \
  oci://$ACR.azurecr.io/helm/broapp \
  --version $CHART_VERSION \
  -n $APP_NS \
  -f values-ingress-tls.yaml \
  --set image.repository=$ACR.azurecr.io/broapp \
  --set image.tag=v2 \
  --atomic \
  --wait \
  --timeout 10m
```

